						<summary>

						<p>A pillar in the Chennakēśavasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1436, Bhāva, Maghā śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1515 A.D., January 30, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a temple <hi rend="italic">(nagaru)</hi> to god Chennakēśava at Pārumaṁchāla by Sāṁtayya, son of Savaram Rāminēḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
